overview: The user requested a comprehensive code review of a sleep
  questionnaire application to verify adherence to acceptance criteria defined
  in the project's documentation. The agent systematically reviewed the
  codebase, examining core functionalities, questionnaire sections, conditional
  logic, and sleep disorder detection mechanisms. The review confirmed that the
  application largely meets the specified requirements, including interactive
  forms, data storage, reporting, and various diagnostic screenings. However,
  the review also highlighted areas for improvement, such as refining algorithms
  for complex circadian rhythm disorders, enhancing data capture for lifestyle
  factors like alcohol consumption, and ensuring precise calculation of metrics
  like the dozing score. The agent provided a detailed breakdown of implemented
  features and identified specific areas requiring further development or
  adjustment.
